			<div class="content" id="post-content-4407347">
									

<p>Your spoiler makes little sense. There are players that are analyzing the game up until 2012, which means the games are played and there are people witnessing the result of the games, otherwise the game would've died down long ago. The nerds that are playing the games should also discovered the probability proportion between Escape Hex and Minotaur early in the game. I think it's also implied that the community simply gradually stopped playing new games after the probability thing is discovered.</p>
<p>Also&#8230;the final thread really shouldn't matter much for the community, beyond fascination to the original copy, that can't really be confirmed since there's also the chance that the kid's copy is the modified one that removed the Minotaur. It's 2012, everyone could get access to old papers and a printer. Say that the original copy don't have Minotaur and it's added by some homebrew rules. So what? It exist now. Same with the aspect of this Wiki: Parawatch is now a thing, O5 is a thing, GOC etc is a thing, that didn't exist in 173.</p>

							</div>

								
					
