				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="3146689"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1572107465 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Oct 2019 16:31</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4407469">
									

<p>I like this premise a lot, and the overall description of the game seems pretty interesting. However, I have to agree with what others stated. It's typical for creepypastas like this one to have a <em>kinda</em> logical explanation for what happened, thus luring us into a false sense of security. But usually, we are given some hints as to why those explanations don't work well enough. Something that doesn't add up. However in this case, the explanation works so well that we don't have a reason to believe that there's something more to this game, and that there's paranormal stuff going on with the minotaur.</p>
<p>Due to this, the creepypasta didn't have much impact on me, and I see this as a problem because creepypastas are meant to evoke some uneasy emotions. Novote.</p>

							</div>

								
					
